From d037823b4ba8888f8c9967dc9772d5f6dc12d610 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lids Labs <55252374+lidslabs@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 00:52:55 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 17/17] lidslabs v0.4.0: revert Swiftfin force-HEVC + DV P7 EL
 strip (0018 pivot)

Device round 2026-07-21 showed both corrections forced Swiftfin onto a
server transcode the players render HDR worse on than their own direct-play:
even a correct HEVC-HDR10 transcode (pure-HDR10 source) failed on AVPlayer
and showed no HDR on VLCKit. Revert force-HEVC-for-Swiftfin and the EL strip;
Swiftfin gets stock handling. Keep the lidslabsSwiftfinClient gate as the
diagnostic anchor for the pending per-engine (VLCKit vs AVPlayer) work. The
0018 removals of the dead TrueHD strip + fMP4 force stand.
---
 .../Controllers/MediaInfoController.cs        | 178 +++++-------------
 1 file changed, 46 insertions(+), 132 deletions(-)

